Simple tests for swing and mix (A2).

Note that (as per Vic Ceder) swing and mix can be done from facing couples.
It is also a three part call (not the two parts "swing" and "mix").

sdr> /program = Program.C1 ; setFormation(Formation.SQUARED_SET); undefined
sdr> heads square thru
| 4B>  3G<  3B>  2G<
| 
| 4G>  1B<  1G>  2B<
sdr> swing and mix
| 1B<  2B<
| 
| 4G>  1G>
| 
| 3G<  2G<
| 
| 4B>  3B>
sdr> do 2/3 of a swing and mix
| 4B>  3B>
| 
| 4G<  1G<
| 
| 3G>  2G>
| 
| 1B<  2B<
sdr> finish swing and mix
| 3G<  2G<
| 
| 1B>  2B>
| 
| 4B<  3B<
| 
| 4G>  1G>
sdr> sides u turn back
| 3G<  2G>
| 
| 1B>  2B<
| 
| 4B>  3B<
| 
| 4G<  1G>
sdr> /// from an inverted line
sdr> swing and mix
| 4G<  1G>
| 
| 4B>  3B<
| 
| 1B>  2B<
| 
| 3G<  2G>
sdr> girls u turn back
| 4G>  1G<
| 
| 4B>  3B<
| 
| 1B>  2B<
| 
| 3G>  2G<
sdr> /// mix from a one-faced line
sdr> finish swing and mix
| 1B<  2B>
| 
| 3G<  2G>
| 
| 4G<  1G>
| 
| 4B<  3B>
sdr> bend the line ; pass the ocean; hinge
| 4G^  4Bv  3B^  1Gv
| 
| 3G^  1Bv  2B^  2Gv
sdr> acey deucey ; swing thru twice
| 4G^  4Bv  3B^  3Gv
| 
| 1G^  1Bv  2B^  2Gv
sdr> right and left grand ; promenade home
|      3Gv  3Bv
| 
| 4B>            2G<
| 
| 4G>            2B<
| 
|      1B^  1G^
sdr> heads pass thru ; side girls u turn back
| 4B>  1B^  1G^  2G>
| 
| 4G<  3Gv  3Bv  2B<
sdr> /// t-boned mix
sdr> finish swing and mix
| 1Gv  4G>  2B>  1Bv
| 
| 3B^  4B<  2G<  3G^
sdr> roll
| 1G>  4Gv  2Bv  1B<
| 
| 3B>  4B^  2G^  3G<
sdr> /exit
